GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 685
Short Title: Rural NC Reinvestment Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Representatives Jeffers, Reives, Cohn, and Pittman (Primary Sponsors).
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Appropriations, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the House
April 3, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO REINVEST IN RURAL NORTH CAROLINA.
3 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
4 SECTION 1. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
5 Environmental Quality the nonrecurring sum of two hundred million dollars ($200,000,000) for
6 the 2025-2026 fiscal year to be used for water and sewer infrastructure grants to units of local
7 government. The Department shall (i) develop guidelines for an application process by units of
8 local government and the allocation of funds granted pursuant to this section and (ii) prioritize
9 projects based on severity of need, efficiency of use of funding, and number of persons served.
10 SECTION 2. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
11 Public Safety the nonrecurring sum of ten million dollars ($10,000,000) for the 2025-2026 fiscal
12 year to be used for grants to municipal and county sheriff and police departments and municipal,
13 county, and volunteer fire departments for needed equipment. The Department shall (i) develop
14 guidelines for an application process by units of local government and eligible departments and
15 for the allocation of funds granted pursuant to this section and (ii) prioritize awarding funds based
16 on age of equipment, severity of need, efficiency of use of funding, and number of persons served
17 by the recipient department.
18 SECTION 3. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
19 Commerce the nonrecurring sum of twenty million dollars ($20,000,000) for the 2025-2026
20 fiscal year to be used for grants to units of local government for land acquisition of sites suitable
21 for economic development uses. The Department shall (i) develop guidelines for an application
22 process by units of local government and for the allocation of funds granted pursuant to this
23 section and (ii) prioritize awarding funds based on likelihood of attracting companies to the site,
24 the development area tier ranking applicable to the unit of local government seeking the award,
25 and the availability of alternative sites developed or ready for development.
26 SECTION 4. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Office of State
27 Budget and Management the nonrecurring sum of five million dollars ($5,000,000) for the
28 2025-2026 fiscal year to be allocated as a directed grant to the North Carolina Medical Society
29 Foundation to be used to further the placement of physicians, physician assistants, and nurse
30 practitioners in underserved areas throughout North Carolina to improve access to care for all
31 citizens of our State.
32 SECTION 5. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
33 Agriculture and Consumer Services the nonrecurring sum of ten million dollars ($10,000,000)
34 for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to be allocated to the North Carolina Agricultural Development and
35 Farmland Preservation Trust Fund to be used for purposes consistent with the Fund.
*H685-v-1*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 SECTION 6. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
2 Public Instruction the nonrecurring sum of two hundred million dollars ($200,000,000) for the
3 2025-2026 fiscal year to be used for grants to local school administrative units in rural areas for
4 new construction and capital improvement needs. The Department shall (i) develop guidelines
5 for an application process by local school administrative units for the allocation of funds granted
6 pursuant to this section and (ii) prioritize awarding funds based on age and condition of school
7 facilities, use of facilities, anticipated life of facilities to be funded, severity of need, efficiency
8 of use of funding, and number of students using the facilities to be funded.
9 SECTION 7. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
10 Information Technology the nonrecurring sum of fifty million dollars ($50,000,000) for the
11 2025-2026 fiscal year to be used as additional, supplemental funding for broadband expansion
12 programs administered by the Department.
13 SECTION 8. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
14 Health and Human Services, Division of Child Development and Early Education, the
15 nonrecurring sum of one hundred million dollars ($100,000,000) for the 2025-2026 fiscal year
16 to be used as additional, supplemental funding for early learning opportunities and programs
17 administered by the Department.
18 SECTION 9. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025.
